sentence: Tuesday's session closes with the NASDAQ Composite Index at 5,275.62.
The total shares traded for the NASDAQ was over 2.13 billion.
Advancers stocks led declining by 1.46 to 1 ratio.
There were 1709 advancers and 1169 decliners for the day.
On the NASDAQ Stock Exchange 134 stocks reached a 52 week high and 18 reaching lows.
The most active, advancers, decliners, unusual volume and most active by dollar volume can be monitored intraday on the Most Active Stocks page.
The NASDAQ 100 index closed up 1.33% for the day; a total of 62.42 points.
Regeneron Pharmaceuticals, Inc. ( REGN ) had the largest percent change down (-3.59%) while JD.com, Inc. ( JD ) had the largest percent change gain rising 11.43%.
The Dow Jones index closed up .29% for the day; a total of 54.37 points.
Home Depot, Inc. (The) ( HD ) had the largest percent change down (-2.56%) while Verizon Communications Inc. ( VZ ) had the largest percent change gain rising 2.58%.
